Supermarkets in Australia lower toilet paper limits per transaction
On Sunday and Saturday afternoon, Australian supermarket chains Woolworths and Coles lowered their limits on purchasing toilet paper to two and one package per transaction in all supermarkets across the country, respectively.
On Monday, ALDI also applied the limit of one package.
These restrictions were posted as messages in the boxes and on the Facebook pages of the networks.
According to reports, consumers were getting supplies out of fear of COVID-19 in case people had to self-isolate.
