This removal may be necessary before surgery or in environments where antibiotic-resistant organisms are very common. To wash your hands before a surgical operation, you need a faucet that can be opened and closed without touching your hands, some chlorhexidine or iodine for washing, sterilized towels to dry your hands after washing, a sterilized scrubbing brush and another sterilized tool to clean under your nails.
